scene.message:
Nanjo: I can't join in talk{nl}
of haunted houses. I've{nl}
never been to one, after all.{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: I wish I could heal{nl}
wounds through sheer{nl}
willpower.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: A haunted house — it's{nl}
just an abandoned building,{nl}
really. We used to play there.{waitkey}{ret}

Mark: It's quiet here. Almost{nl}
like none of it ever{nl}
happened at all.{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: That thing out in{nl}
town...{wait_fr:16} that's not a bear,{nl}
right?{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: But why have Demons{nl}
suddenly started appearing{nl}
all over town?{waitkey}{ret}

Nurse: Did you go to the{nl}
haunted house as a kid too?{waitkey}That place was a real{nl}
playground for children.{waitkey}{ret}

Nurse: A bear showed up, they{nl}
say? A brown one? A polar{nl}
bear? Or maybe a raccoon?{waitkey}{ret}

Doctor: Now then, what'll{nl}
it be?{nl}
{ctl0e:17}{ret}

Doctor: It'll cost 1000 yen.{nl}
Is that all right?{waitkey}{nl}
{ctl0e:0}{ret}

Doctor: A shame, but I can't{nl}
treat you with no money...{nl}
Come back with the fee.{waitkey}{ret}

Doctor: Skimp on treatment{nl}
now, and I hope it won't{nl}
come back to bite you.{waitkey}{ret}

Doctor: I'm a busy man. If{nl}
you've no business here,{nl}
off you go.{waitkey}{ret}
